===Etymology===
From New Latin ''[[orgasmus]],'' derived of the Greek (''[[orgasmos]]''). The word entered English around 1763.

===Noun===
'''orgasm'''
# The [[climax]] or [[peak]] of [[sexual]] pleasure which occurs during sexual activity.

===Verb===
'''orgasm'''
# To have an orgasm.

